Unlocked IMG:
Full format a SD with filesystem FAT32, create a folder named Garmin and copy on it the unlocked gmapsupp.img file map.

Masource version:
Install the package on the PC (CNNANT2013_10Update.msi), then apply the patches.
Then install and patch Mapsource too, it will be useful to select a specific part of the map to send to the device (GPS).

This worked for me on my 7 year old Nuvi.  
I had to delete the original map file  (gmapprom.img: 1 GB)  in order to make space on my 2 GB Nuvi for this new file.  I renamed this new file to gmapsupp.img (it is 1.7GB) and put it in the /Garmin/ directory on the Nuvi.  I also had to delete some unused languages and mp3's to make enough room for it to fit.  It worked like a charm.   Thanks so much for the upload!

As I already wrote in the description, "This map can be viewed on the PC using BaseCamp (USB drive, Garmin folder)."
In other words, copy the map in a Garmin folder of a fully FAT32 formatted pendrive and start BaseCamp with the USB drive plugged in and select the map in the upper left corner of the program.

When updating a 2720 or Garmin with no external memory, use sendmap20 to delete the existing map then use the webupdater to upload the unlocked map.
C:GarminWebUpdaterWebUpdater.exe /upload_file rgn=49 path=C:Garmingmapprom.img -autorun usb /i

Hi Ipmark, I have just downloaded this torrent and wanted to delete the old file from my Nuvi 610, but my Garmin has only 415mb and the download is way larger. I have a micro sd card and an old Europe map that I don't use any more (2 gig), how do I put it onto the sd card. Many Thanks.

Decompress with Winrar the package.
Copy the new gmapsupp.img in the SD's Garmin folder (replace the old one).
Insert the memory card in the Nuvi's USB slot and switch on the GPS, check the new map in (wrench) System > Maps > Maps Info
